 The National Assembly caucus of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has disowned the Ebonyl State governor, Dave Umahi, for defecting to the All Progressives Congress (APC). The legislators also advised the governor to be wary of the Supreme Court’s judgment which frowned at defection of elected office holders when there is no crisis in their political party. Read Also: Ailing PDP hallucinating on ‘third force’ ahead of 2023 APC Sam Egwu, a senator and former governor of Ebonyi State, spoke on behalf of his colleagues at a press conference on Wednesday in Abuja. The news conference was attended by the Senate Minority Leader, Enyinnaya Abaribe. Details coming…